        <mxCell id="fxhD7vzDUJHnhyfsKbxy-593" value="&lt;font face=&quot;Open Sans&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;why a rating property type&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;; background-color: light-dark(#ffffff, var(--ge-dark-color, #121212)); color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Open Sans&quot;&gt;we could just use number, however, this would be useful for distinguishing ratings from plain numbers/integers. perhaps we can have display types for ratings. e..g, display as number, or stars (or custom icons instead of stars), etc&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;size=20;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=11;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;spacingLeft=25;spacingRight=25;" parent="1" vertex="1">
